  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to Building Early Warning &amp; Early Response Systems (BEWERS)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.Conduct PVCAs in the target communities 
2.Conduct conflict sensitivity analysis and peace building analysis 
3.Establishing Peace Committees in the target communities 
4.Formation of GEADOR circles in target communities (to facilitate inclusion of women and other excluded groups in the EWER process
5.Capacity building for peace committees and faith leaders on reconciliatory mechanisms and youths on peaceful co-existence
6.Formation &amp; strengthening of youth committees, women groups &amp; organize youth-driven community service initiatives</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.Early Warning and Early Response systems established in the 3 target communities in Kaura LGA of Kaduna state.
2. Peaceful and effective alternatives to violence established in the 3 target communities in Kaura LGA of Kaduna state.
3. Strengthened the capacity of youths to build resilience to violence in the 3 target communities in Kaura LGA of Kaduna state.</narrative>
  </description>
